CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "Outstanding - Shown conferring with George W. Crawford, center, Most Sovereign Grand Commander of the Northern Jurisdiction of Prince Hall Masons, are left: John G. Lewis, of the Southern Jurisdiction, and Atty. Thurgood Marshall, a 33 degree Mason, also of the Southern Jurisdiction, and chief legal counsel of the NAACP."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Thurgood Marshall, George W. Crawford, and John G. Lewis, standing in Fort Pitt Hotel for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33-Degree Masons
